                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Quoting Ian Jackson (ijackson@chiark.greenend.org.uk):\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> Christian Perrier writes (\"Bug#658416: xfonts-traditional: [debconf_rewrite] Debconf templates and debian/control review proposal\"):\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > I just noticed new or modified debconf templates appearing for this > > package.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> This does not appear to be a bug report. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " Why are you submitting it as > a bug ?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Hello Ian,\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This is a practice we (debian-l10n-english) changed a few months ago :\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "some package maintainers were complaining that our usual reviews of wording in debconf templates and package descriptions were hard for them to track as they were done outside the BTS. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The \"real\" bug report was then sent *after* the review happened.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I agreed with this and we slightly changed the process to open the bug report *before* the review, then instead of CC'ing the maintainer through <package>@p.d.o, we CC the bug report...and at the end of the review, we send the final proposed wording patch in the bug report as well.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I hope this is clearer for you now. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "You're right that, at this moment, there is nothing to change in your package because only the review can tell if there will be something (actually, we always found an improvement to suggest, even with native speakers' packages....:-)).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
